Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Cream 1 cup butter, 1/3 cup confectioner's sugar and vanilla. Sift flour and cornstarch and add to creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes. Watch carefully! Combine 1 cup powdered sugar, melted butter, and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Add enough milk or cream to make spreadable. Spread on warm cookies.